team.description:
Google is known all around the world. Everyone is 'googling', checking on 'maps' and communicating in 'gmail'. For simple users, they are services that just works, but not for us. Developers see much more: APIs, scalability issues, complex technology stacks. And that is what GDG is about.

[Google Developers Group (GDG) Lisbon](https://www.gdglisbon.xyz/) - is open and volunteer geek community who create exciting projects and share experience about Google technologies with a passion.

Our goal is to organize space to connect the best industry experts with Portuguese audience to boost development of IT.

blocks.title: VOST Portugal
blocks.description: VOST Portugal, a group of digital volunteers in emergency situations, counts on a multidisciplinary team that assists the populations in the social networks in case of adverse weather and natural disasters, and in time of peace it dedicates itself to educate the populations towards self-resilience, and to find innovative solutions based on technology and design to help populations. VOST Portugal is part of VOST Europe, which has 8 European countries in its group.
